ChatGPT said:

Awesome—this is totally doable with what you already have in Sheets + Apps Script. Here’s a clean, copy-paste plan that keeps your source of truth in Google Sheets and gives you a lightweight website with:

  • a homepage showing two live leaderboards

    • Sales leaderboard = Sales (MTD) per rep

    • BDC leaderboard = Shows (MTD) per agent

  • each name is clickable → a personal “1on1” page with:

    • their current block-summary stats, and

    • two coaching call picks from their last work day: one ≥ 60s and one < 30s (fallback: longest if no ≥ 60s)

Below are two parts: (A) tiny Apps Script “read-only API” you add to your existing Code.gs, and (B) a minimal website (static HTML+JS) that reads that API.

A) Add these endpoints to your Apps Script (Code.gs)

Paste this whole block at the end of your existing Code.gs. It reuses helpers already in your script (Schedule/Calls/Appt Act parsing, talk-time parsing, etc.) and exposes 2 simple routes:

  • GET ?route=leaderboards

  • GET ?route=person&name=FIRST%20LAST&type=Sales|BDC

javascript
/******************************************************
 * ======== 1) Utilities: JSON response helpers =======
 ******************************************************/
function _json(data, status) {
  return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify(data))
    .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
}
function _err(message, status) {
  return _json({ ok:false, error: String(message) });
}
function _ok(data) {
  return _json({ ok:true, ...data });
}

/******************************************************
 * ======== 2) Leaderboards (Sales & BDC) =============
 * Sales leaderboard → Sales (MTD)
 * BDC leaderboard   → Appts Shown (MTD)
 ******************************************************/
function _buildLeaderboards_(ss) {
  // Reuse your Performance Review readers/aggregators
  const scheduleTypes = getScheduleTypesMap_(ss);
  const isBDC   = n => scheduleTypes[normalizeName_(n)] === 'BDC';
  const isSales = n => scheduleTypes[normalizeName_(n)] === 'Sales';

  // Calls/Text/Sales/Appt Act/Leads maps (your functions)
  const callsMTD     = getCallsRaw_(ss);
  const callsAgg     = aggregateCallsTalk_(callsMTD);
  const apptActMap   = getApptActDataMap_(ss);
  const { textsMap, salesMap } = getUserActMaps_(ss);

  // SALES leaderboard: Sales (MTD)
  const salesLB = [];
  salesMap.forEach((salesCount, name) => {
    if (!isSales(name)) return;
    // keep also useful info for detail page
    const calls = (callsAgg.get(name) || { calls:0 }).calls;
    const texts = textsMap.get(name) || 0;
    salesLB.push({ name, sales: salesCount || 0, calls, texts });
  });
  salesLB.sort((a,b) => b.sales - a.sales || a.name.localeCompare(b.name));

  // BDC leaderboard: Shown (MTD) from Appt Act
  const bdcLB = [];
  apptActMap.forEach((v, name) => {
    if (!isBDC(name)) return;
    const shown = (v && v.shown) ? v.shown : 0;
    const created = (v && v.created) ? v.created : 0;
    bdcLB.push({ name, shows: shown, created });
  });
  bdcLB.sort((a,b) => b.shows - a.shows || a.name.localeCompare(b.name));

  return { salesLB, bdcLB };
}

/******************************************************
 * = 3) Per-person "1on1" block summary + call picks =
 * - Pulls the same metrics used in your 1on1 blocks
 * - Picks 2 calls from the rep's last work day:
 *    • one ≥ 60s (if any)
 *    • one < 30s (if any)
 *   Fallback: longest call if no ≥ 60s exists
 ******************************************************/
function _getPerson1on1_(ss, name, type) {
  const normName = normalizeNameFlexible_(name);
  if (!normName) throw new Error('Missing or invalid name');
  const scheduleTypes = getScheduleTypesMap_(ss);
  const role = scheduleTypes[normName] || type || 'Unknown';

  // Pull shared data
  const callsMTD     = getCallsRaw_(ss);
  const callsAggMap  = aggregateCallsTalkWithDays_(callsMTD); // has perDayStats
  const callsAggTotal= aggregateCallsTalk_(callsMTD);         // totals + talk
  const apptActMap   = getApptActDataMap_(ss);
  const { textsMap, salesMap } = getUserActMaps_(ss);
  const leadsCreatedMap = computeLeadsCreatedMTDByOwner_(ss);

  // Build the block-summary numbers (aligned with your review)
  const callsAgg = callsAggMap.get(normName) || { calls:0, talkMin:0, perDay:new Map(), perDayStats:new Map() };
  const totals   = callsAggTotal.get(normName) || { calls:0, talkMin:0 };
  const ap       = apptActMap.get(normName) || { created:0, due:0, shown:0 };
  const texts    = textsMap.get(normName) || 0;

  const workingDays =
    role === 'BDC'
      ? [...(callsAgg.perDay || new Map()).values()].filter(n => n >= PR_CFG.WORKING_DAY_MIN_CALLS).length
      : countSalesWorkingDaysFromScheduleMTD_ByTeams_(ss, normName, true);

  const avgTalkMin = totals.calls > 0 ? (totals.talkMin / totals.calls) : 0;
  const avgTalkMSS = mmssFromMinutes_(avgTalkMin);

  const block = {
    name: normName,
    type: role,
    workingDays,
    callsMTD: totals.calls,
    avgTalk: avgTalkMSS,
    createdMTD: ap.created,
    dueMTD: ap.due,
    shownMTD: ap.shown,
    textsMTD: texts,
    leadsInNameMTD: leadsCreatedMap.get(normName) || 0,
    salesMTD: salesMap.get(normName) || 0
  };

  // --- Call picks from last work day ---
  const lastKey = getLastWorkDayKey_ByTeamsOrCalls_(ss, normName, callsAgg);
  const picks = _pickTwoCallsFromDate_(ss, normName, lastKey);
  return { block, lastWorkDay: lastKey, picks };
}

// Returns {over, under} with {agent, dateKey, minutes, talkMSS, url, rawSeconds}
// Fallback: if no ≥ 60s exists, 'over' becomes the longest call on that date.
function _pickTwoCallsFromDate_(ss, normName, dateKey) {
  if (!dateKey) return { over:null, under:null };

  const sh = ss.getSheetByName(PR_CFG.CALLS_SHEET);
  if (!sh) return { over:null, under:null };

  const lastRow = sh.getLastRow();
  const lastCol = Math.max(PR_CFG.COL_AGENT, sh.getLastColumn());
  const vals    = sh.getRange(1, 1, lastRow, lastCol).getValues();
  if (vals.length < 2) return { over:null, under:null };

  // detect audio/recording column
  const headerRow = vals[0].map(v => (v ? String(v).toLowerCase() : ''));
  let audioIdx = 43; // default AR
  for (let i = 0; i < headerRow.length; i++) {
    if (/(audio|record|recording|url|link)/.test(headerRow[i])) { audioIdx = i; break; }
  }

  function rowAgent(r)   { return normalizeName_(r[PR_CFG.COL_AGENT - 1]); }
  function rowDateKey(r) {
    const d = coerceDate_(r[PR_CFG.COL_DATE - 1]);
    return d ? Utilities.formatDate(onlyDate_(d), Session.getScriptTimeZone(), 'yyyy-MM-dd') : null;
  }
  function rowMinutes(r) { return parseTalkTime_(r[PR_CFG.COL_TALKTIME - 1]) || 0; }
  function rowUrl(r)     { return (r[audioIdx] && String(r[audioIdx]).trim()) || _guessRecordingUrlFromRow_(vals[0], r) || ''; }

  const entries = [];
  for (let r = 1; r < vals.length; r++) {
    const row = vals[r];
    if (rowAgent(row) !== normName) continue;
    if (rowDateKey(row) !== dateKey) continue;
    const min = rowMinutes(row);
    if (!min || min <= 0) continue;
    entries.push({
      agent: normName,
      dateKey,
      minutes: min,
      rawSeconds: Math.round(min * 60),
      talkMSS: mmssFromMinutes_(min),
      url: rowUrl(row)
    });
  }
  if (!entries.length) return { over:null, under:null };

  const over = entries.filter(e => e.minutes >= 1.0);
  const under = entries.filter(e => e.minutes > 0 && e.minutes < 0.5);

  let pickOver = null;
  if (over.length) {
    pickOver = over[Math.floor(Math.random() * over.length)];
  } else {
    // fallback to longest call that day
    pickOver = entries.slice().sort((a,b) => b.minutes - a.minutes)[0];
  }
  const pickUnder = under.length ? under[Math.floor(Math.random() * under.length)] : null;

  return { over: pickOver, under: pickUnder };
}

/******************************************************
 * ================== 4) Router =======================
 * Publish as Web App (Deploy → Web app → Anyone with link)
 * Routes:
 *  GET ?route=leaderboards
 *  GET ?route=person&name=FIRST%20LAST&type=Sales|BDC
 ******************************************************/
function doGet(e) {
  try {
    const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActive();
    const route = (e && e.parameter && e.parameter.route) ? String(e.parameter.route) : '';
    if (route === 'leaderboards') {
      const { salesLB, bdcLB } = _buildLeaderboards_(ss);
      return _ok({ sales: salesLB, bdc: bdcLB });
    }
    if (route === 'person') {
      const name = (e.parameter.name || '').trim();
      const type = (e.parameter.type || '').trim();
      if (!name) return _err('Missing name');
      const data = _getPerson1on1_(ss, name, type);
      return _ok(data);
    }
    return _err('Unknown route. Try ?route=leaderboards or ?route=person&name=First%20Last&type=Sales');
  } catch (err) {
    return _err(err && err.message ? err.message : String(err));
  }
}

Deploying the API:
Apps Script → Deploy → Manage deployments → New deployment → Web app → Who has access: “Anyone with the link” → Deploy. Copy the Web app URL (we’ll call it GAS_URL below).

This code leans on the exact sheet layout and helpers you’re already using (Schedule, Calls, Appt Act, etc.), including your robust talk-time parsing and last-work-day logic.

B) Minimal website (static HTML + JS)

You can host this anywhere (GitHub Pages, Netlify, S3, local file). It’s one page with hash-routing:

  • #/ → leaderboards

  • #/person/FIRST%20LAST/Sales (or /BDC) → 1on1 page

  1. Create three files in a folder:

index.html

html
<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Store Dashboard — Leaderboards & 1on1s</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <style>
      body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; margin: 0; color: #111; background: #fafafa; }
      header { background:#111; color:#fff; padding:14px 18px; }
      .wrap { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 18px; }
      h1 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 20px; }
      h2 { margin: 18px 0 8px; font-size: 18px; }
      table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; background:#fff; border:1px solid #e8e8e8; }
      th, td { padding: 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; text-align: left; }
      th { background:#fcfcfc; font-weight: 600; }
      a { color: #0a66c2; text-decoration: none; }
      a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
      .two { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 18px; }
      .card { background:#fff; border:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px; }
      .muted { color:#666; font-size: 12px; }
      .pill { display:inline-block; background:#eef6ff; color:#145aa6; padding:3px 8px; border-radius:999px; font-size:12px; }
      .kvs { display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(5, minmax(0,1fr)); gap:10px; margin:10px 0 0; }
      .kv { background:#f9fafb; border:1px solid #eee; border-radius:8px; padding:8px; text-align:center; }
      .kv .n { font-weight:700; font-size:18px; }
      .call { background:#fff; border:1px solid #e8e8e8; border-radius:8px; padding:10px; margin:8px 0; }
      .call a { display:inline-block; margin-top:4px; }
      .back { display:inline-block; margin-bottom:12px; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header><div class="wrap">
      <h1>Store Dashboard</h1>
      <div class="muted">Leaderboards & 1on1s</div>
    </div></header>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div id="app">Loading…</div>
    </div>
    <script>
      // === 1) CONFIG: paste your Apps Script Web App URL here ===
      const GAS_URL = 'PASTE_YOUR_APPS_SCRIPT_WEB_APP_URL_HERE';

      // === 2) Simple router ===
      function route() {
        const hash = location.hash || '#/';
        const parts = hash.slice(2).split('/'); // remove "#/"
        if (parts[0] === '' || parts[0] === 'home') renderHome();
        else if (parts[0] === 'person') {
          const name = decodeURIComponent(parts[1] || '');
          const type = parts[2] || '';
          renderPerson(name, type);
        } else {
          renderNotFound();
        }
      }
      window.addEventListener('hashchange', route);

      // === 3) API helpers ===
      async function apiLeaderboards() {
        const res = await fetch(GAS_URL + '?route=leaderboards');
        return res.json();
      }
      async function apiPerson(name, type) {
        const params = new URLSearchParams({ route: 'person', name, type });
        const res = await fetch(GAS_URL + '?' + params.toString());
        return res.json();
      }
      function linkToPerson(name, type) {
        return '#/person/' + encodeURIComponent(name) + '/' + encodeURIComponent(type || '');
      }

      // === 4) Views ===
      async function renderHome() {
        const root = document.getElementById('app');
        root.innerHTML = 'Loading leaderboards…';
        try {
          const data = await apiLeaderboards();
          if (!data.ok) throw new Error(data.error || 'API error');
          const salesRows = data.sales.map((r, i) => `
            <tr>
              <td>${i+1}</td>
              <td><a href="${linkToPerson(r.name,'Sales')}">${r.name}</a></td>
              <td>${r.sales}</td>
              <td class="muted">${r.calls ?? 0} calls</td>
              <td class="muted">${r.texts ?? 0} texts</td>
            </tr>
          `).join('');
          const bdcRows = data.bdc.map((r, i) => `
            <tr>
              <td>${i+1}</td>
              <td><a href="${linkToPerson(r.name,'BDC')}">${r.name}</a></td>
              <td>${r.shows}</td>
              <td class="muted">${r.created ?? 0} created</td>
            </tr>
          `).join('');

          root.innerHTML = `
            <div class="two">
              <div class="card">
                <h2>Sales Leaderboard <span class="pill">Sales (MTD)</span></h2>
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Rep</th><th>Sales</th><th colspan="2">Extras</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>${salesRows || '<tr><td colspan="5" class="muted">No data</td></tr>'}</tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
              <div class="card">
                <h2>BDC Leaderboard <span class="pill">Shows (MTD)</span></h2>
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Agent</th><th>Shows</th><th>Created</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>${bdcRows || '<tr><td colspan="4" class="muted">No data</td></tr>'}</tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          `;
        } catch (e) {
          root.innerHTML = `<div class="card">Error: ${e.message}</div>`;
        }
      }

      async function renderPerson(name, type) {
        const root = document.getElementById('app');
        root.innerHTML = 'Loading 1on1…';
        try {
          const data = await apiPerson(name, type);
          if (!data.ok) throw new Error(data.error || 'API error');
          const b = data.block;
          const picks = data.picks || {};
          const over = picks.over;
          const under = picks.under;

          root.innerHTML = `
            <a class="back" href="#/">&larr; Back</a>
            <div class="card">
              <h2>${b.name} <span class="pill">${b.type}</span></h2>
              <div class="muted">Last work day: ${data.lastWorkDay || '—'}</div>

              <div class="kvs">
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.workingDays}</div><div class="t">Working Days</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.callsMTD}</div><div class="t">Calls (MTD)</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.avgTalk}</div><div class="t">Avg Talk</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.createdMTD}</div><div class="t">Appts Created</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.shownMTD}</div><div class="t">Appts Shown</div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="kvs" style="margin-top:10px;">
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.dueMTD}</div><div class="t">Appts Due</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.leadsInNameMTD}</div><div class="t">Leads in Name</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.textsMTD}</div><div class="t">Texts</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.salesMTD}</div><div class="t">Sales</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.type}</div><div class="t">Role</div></div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h2>Call Coaching Picks</h2>
              <div class="muted">1 over a minute, 1 under 30 seconds (longest as fallback if none ≥ 60s)</div>
              <div class="call">
                <strong>Over 1:00</strong><br/>
                ${over ? `${over.dateKey} — ${over.talkMSS}${over.url ? `<br/><a href="${over.url}" target="_blank">Play recording</a>`:''}` : '<span class="muted">None</span>'}
              </div>
              <div class="call">
                <strong>Under 0:30</strong><br/>
                ${under ? `${under.dateKey} — ${under.talkMSS}${under.url ? `<br/><a href="${under.url}" target="_blank">Play recording</a>`:''}` : '<span class="muted">None</span>'}
              </div>
            </div>
          `;
        } catch (e) {
          root.innerHTML = `<div class="card">Error: ${e.message}</div>`;
        }
      }

      function renderNotFound() {
        document.getElementById('app').innerHTML = `
          <div class="card">Not found. <a href="#/">Go home</a></div>
        `;
      }

      // Initial render
      route();
    </script>
  </body>
</html>

No bundler needed. Put these files on any static host, set GAS_URL, and you’re live.

Notes & how this maps to your sheets

  • Metrics come from the same functions your Performance Review uses (no new logic to maintain).

  • Leaderboards:

    • Sales = Sales (MTD) from your “User Act” sales map; we also show Calls & Texts as context.

    • BDC = Appts Shown (MTD) from Appt Act (Created shown as context).

  • 1on1 page shows the block KPIs you already coach on (Calls, Avg Talk, Created/Due/Shown, Texts, Leads in Name, Sales) plus two call links from the last work day (your schedule-based last-day logic, falling back to calls history when needed).

  • Call picks rule: one ≥ 60s and one < 30s; if no ≥ 60s, we pick the longest call that day, which matches your request.

If you want this as a Next.js project or want the site protected by a shared password, say the word and I’ll ship that version fully wired to the same GAS_URL.

This implementation reuses your sheet schema, helper functions, and last-work-day + talk-time logic directly from your current script.

      // === 2) Simple router (hash-based) ===
      function route() {
        const hash = location.hash || '#/';
        const parts = hash.slice(2).split('/'); // remove "#/"
        if (parts[0] === '' || parts[0] === 'home') renderHome();
        else if (parts[0] === 'person') {
          const name = decodeURIComponent(parts[1] || '');
          const type = parts[2] || '';
          renderPerson(name, type);
        } else {
          renderNotFound();
        }
      }
      window.addEventListener('hashchange', route);

      // === 3) API helpers ===
      async function apiLeaderboards() {
        const res = await fetch(GAS_URL + '?route=leaderboards', { cache: 'no-store' });
        return res.json();
      }
      async function apiPerson(name, type) {
        const params = new URLSearchParams({ route: 'person', name, type });
        const res = await fetch(GAS_URL + '?' + params.toString(), { cache: 'no-store' });
        return res.json();
      }
      function linkToPerson(name, type) {
        return '#/person/' + encodeURIComponent(name) + '/' + encodeURIComponent(type || '');
      }

      // === 4) Views ===
      async function renderHome() {
        const root = document.getElementById('app');
        root.innerHTML = 'Loading leaderboards…';
        try {
          const data = await apiLeaderboards();
          if (!data.ok) throw new Error(data.error || 'API error');
          const salesRows = data.sales.map((r, i) => `
            <tr>
              <td>${i+1}</td>
              <td><a href="${linkToPerson(r.name,'Sales')}">${r.name}</a></td>
              <td>${r.sales}</td>
              <td class="muted">${r.calls ?? 0} calls</td>
              <td class="muted">${r.texts ?? 0} texts</td>
            </tr>
          `).join('');
          const bdcRows = data.bdc.map((r, i) => `
            <tr>
              <td>${i+1}</td>
              <td><a href="${linkToPerson(r.name,'BDC')}">${r.name}</a></td>
              <td>${r.shows}</td>
              <td class="muted">${r.created ?? 0} created</td>
            </tr>
          `).join('');

          root.innerHTML = `
            <div class="two">
              <div class="card">
                <h2>Sales Leaderboard <span class="pill">Sales (MTD)</span></h2>
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Rep</th><th>Sales</th><th colspan="2">Extras</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>${salesRows || '<tr><td colspan="5" class="muted">No data</td></tr>'}</tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
              <div class="card">
                <h2>BDC Leaderboard <span class="pill">Shows (MTD)</span></h2>
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Agent</th><th>Shows</th><th>Created</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>${bdcRows || '<tr><td colspan="4" class="muted">No data</td></tr>'}</tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          `;
        } catch (e) {
          root.innerHTML = `<div class="card">Error: ${e.message}</div>`;
        }
      }

      async function renderPerson(name, type) {
        const root = document.getElementById('app');
        root.innerHTML = 'Loading 1on1…';
        try {
          const data = await apiPerson(name, type);
          if (!data.ok) throw new Error(data.error || 'API error');
          const b = data.block;
          const picks = data.picks || {};
          const over = picks.over;
          const under = picks.under;

          root.innerHTML = `
            <a class="back" href="#/">&larr; Back</a>
            <div class="card">
              <h2>${b.name} <span class="pill">${b.type}</span></h2>
              <div class="muted">Last work day: ${data.lastWorkDay || '—'}</div>

              <div class="kvs">
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.workingDays}</div><div class="t">Working Days</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.callsMTD}</div><div class="t">Calls (MTD)</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.avgTalk}</div><div class="t">Avg Talk</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.createdMTD}</div><div class="t">Appts Created</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.shownMTD}</div><div class="t">Appts Shown</div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="kvs" style="margin-top:10px;">
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.dueMTD}</div><div class="t">Appts Due</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.leadsInNameMTD}</div><div class="t">Leads in Name</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.textsMTD}</div><div class="t">Texts</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.salesMTD}</div><div class="t">Sales</div></div>
                <div class="kv"><div class="n">${b.type}</div><div class="t">Role</div></div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h2>Call Coaching Picks</h2>
              <div class="muted">1 over a minute, 1 under 30 seconds (longest as fallback if none ≥ 60s)</div>
              <div class="call">
                <strong>Over 1:00</strong><br/>
                ${over ? `${over.dateKey} — ${over.talkMSS}${over.url ? `<br/><a href="${over.url}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Play recording</a>`:''}` : '<span class="muted">None</span>'}
              </div>
              <div class="call">
                <strong>Under 0:30</strong><br/>
                ${under ? `${under.dateKey} — ${under.talkMSS}${under.url ? `<br/><a href="${under.url}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Play recording</a>`:''}` : '<span class="muted">None</span>'}
              </div>
            </div>
          `;
        } catch (e) {
          root.innerHTML = `<div class="card">Error: ${e.message}</div>`;
        }
      }

      function renderNotFound() {
        document.getElementById('app').innerHTML = `
          <div class="card">Not found. <a href="#/">Go home</a></div>
        `;
      }

      // Initial render
      route();
    </script>

function doGet(e) {
  try {
    const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActive();

    if (route === 'leaderboards') {
      const { salesLB, bdcLB } = _buildLeaderboards_(ss);

  }
}

/** Group an agent's calls by date (yyyy-MM-dd), newest first */
function _getAgentCallsByDate_(ss, normName) {
  const sh = ss.getSheetByName(PR_CFG.CALLS_SHEET);
  if (!sh) return [];

  const lastRow = sh.getLastRow();
  const lastCol = Math.max(PR_CFG.COL_AGENT, sh.getLastColumn());
  const vals    = sh.getRange(1, 1, lastRow, lastCol).getValues();
  if (vals.length < 2) return [];

  // find audio/recording column once
  const headerRow = vals[0].map(v => (v ? String(v).toLowerCase() : ''));
  let audioIdx = 43; // default AR
  for (let i = 0; i < headerRow.length; i++) {
    if (/(audio|record|recording|url|link)/.test(headerRow[i])) { audioIdx = i; break; }
  }

  function rowAgent(r)   { return normalizeName_(r[PR_CFG.COL_AGENT - 1]); }
  function rowDateKey(r) {
    const d = coerceDate_(r[PR_CFG.COL_DATE - 1]);
    return d ? Utilities.formatDate(onlyDate_(d), Session.getScriptTimeZone(), 'yyyy-MM-dd') : null;
  }
  function rowMinutes(r) { return parseTalkTime_(r[PR_CFG.COL_TALKTIME - 1]) || 0; }
  function rowUrl(r)     { return (r[audioIdx] && String(r[audioIdx]).trim()) || _guessRecordingUrlFromRow_(vals[0], r) || ''; }

  // group entries by date
  const byDate = new Map();
  for (let r = 1; r < vals.length; r++) {
    const row = vals[r];
    if (rowAgent(row) !== normName) continue;

    const dateKey = rowDateKey(row);
    const min     = rowMinutes(row);
    if (!dateKey || !min || min <= 0) continue;

    const entry = {
      agent: normName,
      dateKey,
      minutes: min,
      rawSeconds: Math.round(min * 60),
      talkMSS: mmssFromMinutes_(min),
      url: rowUrl(row)
    };
    if (!byDate.has(dateKey)) byDate.set(dateKey, []);
    byDate.get(dateKey).push(entry);
  }

  // sort newest -> oldest
  const keys = [...byDate.keys()].sort((a, b) => new Date(b) - new Date(a));
  return keys.map(k => ({ dateKey: k, entries: byDate.get(k) }));
}

/**
 * Pick two calls from the most recent date WITH recordings.
 * Priority:
 *   - try preferredDateKey first (last work day)
 *   - otherwise walk back to the latest prior date where the agent has calls
 * Picks: one ≥ 60s (fallback longest), one < 30s if available.
 */
function _pickTwoCallsFromRecent_(ss, normName, preferredDateKey) {
  const daily = _getAgentCallsByDate_(ss, normName);
  if (!daily.length) return { over: null, under: null };

  // reorder so preferredDateKey (if present) is considered first
  const ordered = daily.slice();
  if (preferredDateKey) {
    const i = ordered.findIndex(d => d.dateKey === preferredDateKey);
    if (i > 0) { const [item] = ordered.splice(i, 1); ordered.unshift(item); }
  }

  for (const day of ordered) {
    const entries = day.entries || [];
    if (!entries.length) continue;

    const over  = entries.filter(e => e.minutes >= 1.0);
    const under = entries.filter(e => e.minutes > 0 && e.minutes < 0.5);

    let pickOver  = over.length ? over[Math.floor(Math.random() * over.length)]
                                : entries.slice().sort((a,b) => b.minutes - a.minutes)[0];
    let pickUnder = under.length ? under[Math.floor(Math.random() * under.length)] : null;

    // ensure dateKey is set on returned objects
    if (pickOver)  pickOver.dateKey  = day.dateKey;
    if (pickUnder) pickUnder.dateKey = day.dateKey;

    // return as soon as we have at least one pick from a day that has recordings
    if (pickOver || pickUnder) return { over: pickOver, under: pickUnder };
  }
  return { over: null, under: null };
}

/** Group an agent's calls by date (yyyy-MM-dd), newest first */
function _getAgentCallsByDate_(ss, normName) {
  const sh = ss.getSheetByName(PR_CFG.CALLS_SHEET);
  if (!sh) return [];

  const lastRow = sh.getLastRow();
  const lastCol = Math.max(PR_CFG.COL_AGENT, sh.getLastColumn());
  const vals    = sh.getRange(1, 1, lastRow, lastCol).getValues();
  if (vals.length < 2) return [];

  // detect audio/recording column once
  const headerRow = vals[0].map(v => (v ? String(v).toLowerCase() : ''));
  let audioIdx = 43; // default AR
  for (let i = 0; i < headerRow.length; i++) {
    if (/(audio|record|recording|url|link)/.test(headerRow[i])) { audioIdx = i; break; }
  }

  function rowAgent(r)   { return normalizeName_(r[PR_CFG.COL_AGENT - 1]); }
  function rowDateKey(r) {
    const d = coerceDate_(r[PR_CFG.COL_DATE - 1]);
    return d ? Utilities.formatDate(onlyDate_(d), Session.getScriptTimeZone(), 'yyyy-MM-dd') : null;
  }
  function rowMinutes(r) { return parseTalkTime_(r[PR_CFG.COL_TALKTIME - 1]) || 0; }
  function rowUrl(r)     { return (r[audioIdx] && String(r[audioIdx]).trim()) || _guessRecordingUrlFromRow_(vals[0], r) || ''; }

  // group entries by date
  const byDate = new Map();
  for (let r = 1; r < vals.length; r++) {
    const row = vals[r];
    if (rowAgent(row) !== normName) continue;

    const dk = rowDateKey(row);
    const min = rowMinutes(row);
    if (!dk || !min || min <= 0) continue;

    const entry = {
      agent: normName,
      dateKey: dk,
      minutes: min,
      rawSeconds: Math.round(min * 60),
      talkMSS: mmssFromMinutes_(min),
      url: rowUrl(row)
    };
    if (!byDate.has(dk)) byDate.set(dk, []);
    byDate.get(dk).push(entry);
  }

  // newest -> oldest
  const keys = [...byDate.keys()].sort((a, b) => new Date(b) - new Date(a));
  return keys.map(k => ({ dateKey: k, entries: byDate.get(k) }));
}

/**
 * Pick two calls from the most recent date WITH recordings.
 * Priority:
 *  - try preferredDateKey (last work day)
 *  - else walk backward to the latest prior date with calls
 * Picks: one ≥60s (fallback: longest), one <30s if available.
 */
function _pickTwoCallsFromRecent_(ss, normName, preferredDateKey) {
  const daily = _getAgentCallsByDate_(ss, normName);
  if (!daily.length) return { over: null, under: null };

  // consider preferred day first
  const ordered = daily.slice();
  if (preferredDateKey) {
    const i = ordered.findIndex(d => d.dateKey === preferredDateKey);
    if (i > 0) { const [it] = ordered.splice(i, 1); ordered.unshift(it); }
  }

  for (const day of ordered) {
    const entries = day.entries || [];
    if (!entries.length) continue;

    const over  = entries.filter(e => e.minutes >= 1.0);
    const under = entries.filter(e => e.minutes > 0 && e.minutes < 0.5);

    let pickOver  = over.length ? over[Math.floor(Math.random() * over.length)]
                                : entries.slice().sort((a,b) => b.minutes - a.minutes)[0];
    let pickUnder = under.length ? under[Math.floor(Math.random() * under.length)] : null;

    if (pickOver)  pickOver.dateKey  = day.dateKey;
    if (pickUnder) pickUnder.dateKey = day.dateKey;

    if (pickOver || pickUnder) return { over: pickOver, under: pickUnder };
  }
  return { over: null, under: null };
}

function _getPerson1on1_(ss, name, type) {
  const normName = normalizeNameFlexible_(name);
  if (!normName) throw new Error('Missing or invalid name');
  const scheduleTypes = getScheduleTypesMap_(ss);
  const role = scheduleTypes[normName] || type || 'Unknown';

  // Pull shared data
  const callsMTD     = getCallsRaw_(ss);
  const callsAggMap  = aggregateCallsTalkWithDays_(callsMTD); // has perDayStats
  const callsAggTotal= aggregateCallsTalk_(callsMTD);         // totals + talk
  const apptActMap   = getApptActDataMap_(ss);
  const { textsMap, salesMap } = getUserActMaps_(ss);
  const leadsCreatedMap = computeLeadsCreatedMTDByOwner_(ss);

  const callsAgg = callsAggMap.get(normName) || { calls:0, talkMin:0, perDay:new Map(), perDayStats:new Map() };
  const totals   = callsAggTotal.get(normName) || { calls:0, talkMin:0 };
  const ap       = apptActMap.get(normName) || { created:0, due:0, shown:0 };
  const texts    = textsMap.get(normName) || 0;

  const workingDays =
    role === 'BDC'
      ? [...(callsAgg.perDay || new Map()).values()].filter(n => n >= PR_CFG.WORKING_DAY_MIN_CALLS).length
      : countSalesWorkingDaysFromScheduleMTD_ByTeams_(ss, normName, true);

  const avgTalkMin = totals.calls > 0 ? (totals.talkMin / totals.calls) : 0;
  const avgTalkMSS = mmssFromMinutes_(avgTalkMin);

  const block = {
    name: normName,
    type: role,
    workingDays,
    callsMTD: totals.calls,
    avgTalk: avgTalkMSS,
    createdMTD: ap.created,
    dueMTD: ap.due,
    shownMTD: ap.shown,
    textsMTD: texts,
    leadsInNameMTD: leadsCreatedMap.get(normName) || 0,
    salesMTD: salesMap.get(normName) || 0
  };

  // --- Call picks (now falls back to most recent day with recordings) ---
  const lastKey = getLastWorkDayKey_ByTeamsOrCalls_(ss, normName, callsAgg);
  const picks = _pickTwoCallsFromRecent_(ss, normName, lastKey);

  return { block, lastWorkDay: lastKey, picks };
}

/** Group an agent's calls by date (yyyy-MM-dd), newest first */
function _getAgentCallsByDate_(ss, normName) {
  const sh = ss.getSheetByName(PR_CFG.CALLS_SHEET);
  if (!sh) return [];

  const lastRow = sh.getLastRow();
  const lastCol = Math.max(PR_CFG.COL_AGENT, sh.getLastColumn());
  const vals    = sh.getRange(1, 1, lastRow, lastCol).getValues();
  if (vals.length < 2) return [];

  const headerRow = vals[0].map(v => (v ? String(v).toLowerCase() : ''));
  let audioIdx = 43;
  for (let i = 0; i < headerRow.length; i++) {
    if (/(audio|record|recording|url|link)/.test(headerRow[i])) { audioIdx = i; break; }
  }

  function rowAgent(r)   { return normalizeName_(r[PR_CFG.COL_AGENT - 1]); }
  function rowDateKey(r) {
    const d = coerceDate_(r[PR_CFG.COL_DATE - 1]);
    return d ? Utilities.formatDate(onlyDate_(d), Session.getScriptTimeZone(), 'yyyy-MM-dd') : null;
  }
  function rowMinutes(r) { return parseTalkTime_(r[PR_CFG.COL_TALKTIME - 1]) || 0; }
  function rowUrl(r)     { return (r[audioIdx] && String(r[audioIdx]).trim()) || _guessRecordingUrlFromRow_(vals[0], r) || ''; }

  const byDate = new Map();
  for (let r = 1; r < vals.length; r++) {
    const row = vals[r];
    if (rowAgent(row) !== normName) continue;

    const dateKey = rowDateKey(row);
    const min     = rowMinutes(row);
    if (!dateKey || !min || min <= 0) continue;

    const entry = {
      agent: normName,
      dateKey,
      minutes: min,
      rawSeconds: Math.round(min * 60),
      talkMSS: mmssFromMinutes_(min),
      url: rowUrl(row)
    };
    if (!byDate.has(dateKey)) byDate.set(dateKey, []);
    byDate.get(dateKey).push(entry);
  }

  const keys = [...byDate.keys()].sort((a, b) => new Date(b) - new Date(a));
  return keys.map(k => ({ dateKey: k, entries: byDate.get(k) }));
}

/** Summarize Calls & Avg Talk (and Sales if you later wire it) for a given date */
function _summarizeDayForAgent_(ss, normName, dateKey) {
  if (!dateKey) return { dateKey: null, calls: 0, avgTalkMSS: '0:00', sales: null };
  const daily = _getAgentCallsByDate_(ss, normName);
  const day = daily.find(d => d.dateKey === dateKey);
  if (!day || !day.entries || !day.entries.length) {
    return { dateKey, calls: 0, avgTalkMSS: '0:00', sales: null };
  }
  const calls = day.entries.length;
  const avgMin = day.entries.reduce((s,e)=>s+e.minutes,0) / calls;
  return { dateKey, calls, avgTalkMSS: mmssFromMinutes_(avgMin), sales: null /* TODO: wire daily sales if available */ };
}

Replace your previous picks helper with this one (note the shortest-call fallback and the returned usedDate):

javascript
/**
 * Pick two calls from the most recent date WITH recordings.
 * Priority:
 *   - try preferredDateKey (last work day)
 *   - else walk backward to the latest prior date with calls
 * Picks:
 *   - Over: one ≥ 60s (fallback = longest on that day)
 *   - Under: one < 30s (fallback = shortest on that day)
 */
function _pickTwoCallsFromRecent_(ss, normName, preferredDateKey) {
  const daily = _getAgentCallsByDate_(ss, normName);
  if (!daily.length) return { over: null, under: null, usedDate: null };

  const ordered = daily.slice();
  if (preferredDateKey) {
    const i = ordered.findIndex(d => d.dateKey === preferredDateKey);
    if (i > 0) { const [item] = ordered.splice(i, 1); ordered.unshift(item); }
  }

  for (const day of ordered) {
    const entries = day.entries || [];
    if (!entries.length) continue;

    const over  = entries.filter(e => e.minutes >= 1.0);
    const under = entries.filter(e => e.minutes > 0 && e.minutes < 0.5);

    const pickOver  = over.length
      ? over[Math.floor(Math.random() * over.length)]
      : entries.slice().sort((a,b) => b.minutes - a.minutes)[0];

    const pickUnder = under.length
      ? under[Math.floor(Math.random() * under.length)]
      : entries.slice().sort((a,b) => a.minutes - b.minutes)[0]; // shortest fallback

    if (pickOver)  pickOver.dateKey  = day.dateKey;
    if (pickUnder) pickUnder.dateKey = day.dateKey;

    return { over: pickOver, under: pickUnder, usedDate: day.dateKey };
  }
  return { over: null, under: null, usedDate: null };
}

function _getPerson1on1_(ss, name, type) {
  const normName = normalizeNameFlexible_(name);
  if (!normName) throw new Error('Missing or invalid name');
  const scheduleTypes = getScheduleTypesMap_(ss);
  const role = scheduleTypes[normName] || type || 'Unknown';

  const callsMTD     = getCallsRaw_(ss);
  const callsAggMap  = aggregateCallsTalkWithDays_(callsMTD);
  const callsAggTotal= aggregateCallsTalk_(callsMTD);
  const apptActMap   = getApptActDataMap_(ss);
  const { textsMap, salesMap } = getUserActMaps_(ss);
  const leadsCreatedMap = computeLeadsCreatedMTDByOwner_(ss);

  const callsAgg = callsAggMap.get(normName) || { calls:0, talkMin:0, perDay:new Map(), perDayStats:new Map() };
  const totals   = callsAggTotal.get(normName) || { calls:0, talkMin:0 };
  const ap       = apptActMap.get(normName) || { created:0, due:0, shown:0 };
  const texts    = textsMap.get(normName) || 0;

  const workingDays =
    role === 'BDC'
      ? [...(callsAgg.perDay || new Map()).values()].filter(n => n >= PR_CFG.WORKING_DAY_MIN_CALLS).length
      : countSalesWorkingDaysFromScheduleMTD_ByTeams_(ss, normName, true);

  const avgTalkMin = totals.calls > 0 ? (totals.talkMin / totals.calls) : 0;
  const block = {
    name: normName,
    type: role,
    workingDays,
    callsMTD: totals.calls,
    avgTalk: mmssFromMinutes_(avgTalkMin),
    createdMTD: ap.created,
    dueMTD: ap.due,
    shownMTD: ap.shown,
    textsMTD: texts,
    leadsInNameMTD: leadsCreatedMap.get(normName) || 0,
    salesMTD: salesMap.get(normName) || 0
  };

  const lastKey = getLastWorkDayKey_ByTeamsOrCalls_(ss, normName, callsAgg);
  const picks = _pickTwoCallsFromRecent_(ss, normName, lastKey);
  const lastDay = _summarizeDayForAgent_(ss, normName, lastKey);

  return { block, lastWorkDay: lastKey, lastDay: lastDay, picks: picks };
}
